            , the number of active stations is another determinant affecting the degree of competitiveness of the media market. We introduce this additional measure in order to evaluate how the profitability of horizontal mergers in this market depends on the relative size of the merged entity in comparison to the size of the entire market, as measured by its number of participants.7

